{"id":14881820,"mediaExerciseId":"45e09b0b-ef60-4b2a-b673-040bf7b1b0cb","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612487,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":786,"solutions":[{"id":6004732,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are tasked to decide what a firm should do to address the risk that they are facing in terms of their production.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Since the firm is a large producer of oil, then it needs to be aware of the possible movements in the price of oil. In order to offset/negate the possible losses due to the decrease in price, they need to sell futures contracts. This will allow them to still make profit despite the lower prices in oil.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/75c64850ca7608df6b467cf1f5b1305b/2f3ccbe602fab7080995b24c861563ae/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/75c64850ca7608df6b467cf1f5b1305b/2f3ccbe602fab7080995b24c861563ae/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"One reason why it is not possible to achieve a flat risk profile is because a futures contract is standardized. This means that the company may not be able to include the exact amount and quantity they want to sell in the contract. \n\nAnother reason is that there are only a few large producers of oil so finding a company that is willing to buy their contract may be a challenge. \n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":216,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/75c64850ca7608df6b467cf1f5b1305b/306c557ad9ac57af585b659e57172d15/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/75c64850ca7608df6b467cf1f5b1305b/306c557ad9ac57af585b659e57172d15/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"29df88ab-269d-475b-b3e5-a6e62141cc1a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881821,"exerciseName":"5","page":786,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"fe8c21e3-fe12-47c2-b426-72a91e007a70","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-critical-thinking-questions-5-fe8c21e3-fe12-47c2-b426-72a91e007a70"},{"id":14881822,"exerciseName":"6","page":786,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"4647fc73-4e39-4b43-99c4-772707e274a2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-critical-thinking-questions-6-4647fc73-4e39-4b43-99c4-772707e274a2"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881819,"exerciseName":"3","page":786,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"59c29c8a-a350-4106-be1a-10d6c4869cd5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of